<CENTER><H2>Home Life Books
</H2></CENTER>
<IMG SRC="HLBooks1.gif"><P>
<B>NEW! Bear's Guide to Earning Non-Traditional College Degrees (12th ed.) $27.95</B><BR>
1996 edition! Save thousands of dollars on your Bachelor's, Master's, or PhD with this guide 
to non-traditional & off-campus programs. Many degrees available without ever setting foot 
on a college campus. Evaluates 100s of institutions. Also lists all known diploma mills, 
so you won't lose your money to these scams. Huge book, 300 pages. <B>#BG</B><P>
<B>NEW! Walston's Guide to Earning Religious Degrees Non-Traditionally $20</B><BR>
Is your pastor's degree from a diploma mill? Will that seminary by correspondence program 
bring you joy or shame? Find out who's legit and who's not. <B>#WG</B><P>
<B>The Way Home $9.99</B><BR>
Biblical support for moms at home by Mary Pride, publisher of PHS. Over 80,000 copies sold. <B>#TWH</B><P>
<B>All the Way Home $13.99</B><BR>
The sequel. Practical how-tos for moms at home. Packed with tips from readers of Mary's first newsletter.  <B>#AWH</B><P>
<B>Prides' Guide to Educational Software $25</B><BR>
Over 750 programs reviewed & rated. John C. Dvorak, the world's most famous computer columnist, 
says, "There is nothing like it.  Highest recommendation. Five stars." <B>#PG</B><P>
<B>Schoolproof $8.99</B><BR>
How to home school the E-Z way. Teaching how-tos, motivation, eliminating twaddle, and much more. By Mary Pride. <B>#SP</B><P>
<B>Christian Family Living $12.95</B><BR>
Best book of its kind. Topics include how to raise virtuous children, courtship, singlehood, 
marriage, home and church. Also solid advice on what to do when everything goes wrong. Conservative and gracious. <B>#CFL</B><P>
<IMG SRC="HLBooks2.gif"><P>
<B>Training Children in Godliness - Softcover #TCG $4.95; Hardcover #TCGH $8</B><BR>
Fantastic19th-century advice from a best-selling author of that time. Stresses affection & 
sympathy, reminds us that this is not the same thing as indulgence, which "never awakens 
gratitude or love in the heart of a child." Gems on every page.<P>
<B>Creative Play Areas $9.95</B><BR>
Give your children the childhood you wish you'd had. Simple instructions for creating 
inexpensive play AREAS and costumes for your children. Rubber tire obstacle course, anyone? <B>#CPA</B><P>
<B>Hints on Child Training $9.95</B><BR>
This book was written over a century ago by Elisabeth Elliott's grandfather, a leader in 
the original Sunday School movement and a father of eight. Short chapters train your child 
to be courteous, to deny himself, not to pester. How to train (not break) his will. Choosing 
proper friends and amusements. How to win your child's respect and obedience. Lots more. <B>#HCT</B><P>
<B>What the Bible Says About Marriage, Divorce & Remarriage  $4.95</B><BR>
Why remarriage is unscriptural. Why adultery, desertion, and getting saved don't nullify 
marriage vows. By the same author as Christian Family Living. Traditional Mennonite teaching, 
as practiced for 100s of years. <B>#MDR</B><P>
<B>The Bible and Birth Control  $4.95</B><BR>
What famous Protestant leaders of the past had to say on the subject. Surprisethey were against it! <B>#BBC</B><P>
<B>Survivor's Guide to Home Schooling  $8.99</B><BR>
What to do when the kids won't do their schoolwork and the laundry is piling up. Detailed, 
practical advice on how to handle everyday homeschool quandaries. If you're feeling disorganized, 
this is the book for you!  <B>#SG</B><P>
<B>Save! Flirting with the Devil was $7.99, now $4.99 while supplies last!</B><BR>
Your children need to know the difference between MTV-generation Christianity and the real 
thing. Buy this book and learn the tell-tale signs. <B>#FD</B><P>
<B>Child Abuse Industry $8.95</B><BR>
We only have 100 copies of this book left. Over 80,000 have been sold. Don't be naive about 
this subject: one out of three families gets hotlined. <B>#CAI</B><P>
