<TITLE>Reiman Country Store Books</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFF3B3>
<CENTER><H2>How to Have a</H2>
<H1>Happy Family</H1></CENTER>
Escape today's pressures with these wonderful books from the publishers of COUNTRY 
magazine! See how American families played together and worked together, when this 
country was a better place . . . and how the Amish do it today.<P>
<DL>
<DT><B>NEW! 1,628 Country Shortcuts from 1,628 Country People $16.95</B>
<DD>The most helpful book you've ever read! The best time-saving money-saving home hints 
gleaned from years of country magazines. <B>#CSCP</B><P>

<DT><B>NEW! Goodbye, Boise ... Hello, Alaska $14.95</B>
<DD>True story of a family's move to a remote island ranch where the mail is only delivered 
four times a year.  <B>#GB</B><P>

<DT><B>NEW! The Good Land: Farm Families Remember $16.95</B>	
<DD>Hundreds of vintage black-and-white and color photos, plus hundreds of heartfelt 
recollections celebrating strong values, hard work, and love of the land. <B>#GL</B><P>

<DT><B>NEW! Rugged Hills, Gentle Folk $14.95</B>
<DD>In the Big Pine Valley you can leave your doors unlocked and your car keys in the 
ignition. Follow the real-life adventures of veterinarian Bill Weber as he meets his 
new Big Pine Valley neighbors, both human and animal. <B>#RH</B><P>

<DT><B>NEW! Stickball, Streetcars and Saturday Matinees $14.95</B>
<DD>Growing up innocent and happy in the city . . . in the 1930s! Your kids deserve this 
look at a simpler time, so they can see what American cities once were like . . . and 
what they could be again.  <B>#SS</B><P>

<DT><B>NEW! Tales of Teams: Heartwarming Memories of Horses and Mules $14.95</B>
<DD>Amazing and amusing memories of the country's best work animals through the personal true 
stories of folks around the country. <B>#TT</B><P>

<DT><B>When Families Made Memories Together $14.95</B>
<DD>If you're looking for uplifting reading, look no further. This book actually brought tears 
to my eyes! People from all over America share their heartwarming recollections of family 
life in "the good old days." Lots of great ideas and inspiration for YOUR family, too! 100s 
of great photos! <B>#FMM</B><P>

<DT><B>A Day in the Life of the Amish $14.95</B>
<DD>Home worship, buggies, barnraisings, & more! More than 60 Amish families kept a "diary" for 
one day. This is the result, complemented by photos of their settlements, homes, and farms. 
Great for a unit study of Amish culture. <B>#DLA</B><P>

<DT><B>Horsepower $11.95</B>
<DD>Over 300 B&W photos and text celebrate the farm horse. <B>#HP</B><P>

<DT><B>"We Pulled Together . . .  and Won!"  $14.95</B>
<DD>From Pearl Harbor to V-J Day, vivid memories. Not a "war" bookthis is about how people lived 
through those years. Great for your American history studies. <B>#PTW</B><P>

<DT><B>"We Had Everything but Money" $14.95</B>
<DD>The Great Depression wasn't depressing if what you cared about was family and community. The 
readers of Reminisce magazine contributed hundreds of personal memories and cherished photos. 
Will bring a smile to your face and a lump to your throat. <B>#WEM</B><P>

<DT><B>God's Country $14.95</B>
<DD>Stunning photos of the USA, uplifting looks at good people and communities. If you're starting 
to believe America is all about crime and family breakdown, you need to read this book. Great 
for geography lessons, too! <B>#GC</B><P>
</DL>
<P>

What could be better than this collection of great down-home recipes for your kitchen! Each 
COUNTRY recipe book is spiral-bound, packed with luscious full-color photos of the tasty dishes 
YOU'LL soon be creating in your very own kitchen!
<DL>
<DT><B>NEW! A Day in an Amish Kitchen $14.95</B>
<DD>Over 200 authentic (and simple!) recipes, plus fascinating first-hand details of Amish life and 
lots of color photos. <B>#DAK</B><P>

<DT><B>NEW! Taste of Home Recipe Book $12.95</B>
<DD>Over 530 tried-and-true recipes from the country's most popular food magazine. <B>#TOH</B><P>

<DT><B>NEW! A Taste of the Country 8 $9.95</B>
<DD>The new edition, with over 300 of the best recipes from 3 country magazines! Spiral-bound with 
color photos. <B>#TC8</B> Also available: Taste of the Country 1 <B>(#TC1)</B> through Taste of the Country 7 
<B>(#TC7). $9.95 each.</B><P>

<DT><B>The Best of Country Cooking	$24.95</B>
<DD>Over 750 family-pleasing recipes! Huge treasury of taste-tested recipes. Hard cover, spiral-bound. <B>#BCC</B><P>

<DT><B>Bountiful Harvest  $9.95</B>
<DD>300 recipes for your home-grown fruits & veggies. One chapter per veggie. Many full-color photos.  <B>#BH</B><P>

<DT><B>Country Ground Beef $9.95</B>
<DD>300 new recipes, including over 30 just for meatloaf! Skillet suppers like Aunt Fran's Goulash. Main-dish 
soups like Chuck Wagon Chowder. Oven meals like Barbecued Beef and Beans. Plus sandwiches, meat pies, and 
more. Many full-color photos, taste-tested recipes, spiral-bound. <B>#CGF</B><P>

<DT><B>Grandma's Great Desserts	$10.95</B>
<DD>Ozark Blueberry Pie, yum! Over 300 heirloom recipes. Packed with photos, plus bonus "secret" hints and the 
heartwarming stories behind these treats. <B>#GGD</B><P>

