<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Dolls & Dreams</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFF3B3>
<CENTER><H2>Dolls & Dreams
</H2></CENTER>
<P>
Childhood has a glow, when children are allowed to fill their playtime with noble thoughts. 
Brave knights and kind ladies . . . comforting grandmas and patient grandpas . . . 
a lovely dollhouse to decorate and redecorate . . . darling baby dolls to cuddle and tuck into bed. 
These beloved childhood toys inspire children to love what is good and worthy, and to 
aspire to grow up wise and good. A gentle refuge from our overstimulated modern world.<P>

<IMG SRC="DollHouse.gif" ALIGN=left><B>Pine Country Cottage, $99</B>
This dreamy dollhouse is built to take a lot of rugged play. Handcrafted from solid pine, 
ours has stood up to several years of play in our house, where our nine rough-'n-tumble 
children have already broken several less-durable dollhouses to flinders. Buttery-soft 
wood, natural finish, a romantic play environment for years of treasured memories. 16" high 
x 19" wide x 13" deep. <B>#PCC</B><BR CLEAR="left"><P>

<IMG SRC="MedFurn.gif" ALIGN=left>
<B>Pine Table and Chair Set, $25</B><BR>
Small dolls enjoy a spot of 
tea and conversation around 
this natural wood table. <B>#PTC<BR CLEAR="left"><P>

<IMG SRC="DollFurn.gif" ALIGN=left>Pine Doll Bed, $49, #PDB<BR>
Pine Doll Couch, $49, #PDC<BR>
Pine Doll Armchair, $39, #PDA</B><BR>
The perfect size for your "American Girls" or other 16" dolls. Handcrafted solid pine 
with a natural wood finish, and romantic tree shapes in the headboard and backs. Made of 
chunky doll-sized logs, very strong. 20" x 12" x 10".<P>

<B>Mattress & Pillow, $19, #DMP<BR>
Couch Cushion, $9.50, #DCC<BR>
Armchair Cushion, $7.50, #DAC</B><BR>
100 percent cotton stuffed with real feathers. Print fabric. Machine washable. <P>
<B>Pine Doll Wardrobe, $79, #PDW<BR>
Closet Hangers (pkg of 6), $6.50, #CH</B><BR>
Ample storage for treasured doll clothes in this 19" x 11" x 11" wardrobe! Wooden tree-shaped 
cutouts in door, so you can look into closet. Rod for hangers, and a bottom drawer. </DL><P>

<IMG SRC="FingPupp.gif" ALIGN=left><B>Old World Finger Puppet Kits, $15 each. Two puppets per kit.</B><BR>
We have found that finger puppets are ideal toys. They are small enough to live in houses made of blocks, or 
in our own Pine Country Cottage. Compared to full-size dolls, they are inexpensive, and without that nasty 
plastic smell. And now you can make your own beautiful finger puppets. Children prefer the Middle Ages of 
knights and damsels, and that's what you get. Each kit includes everything you need to make two character 
puppets, finished size 4" tall. <BR>Take your pick of the 
<B>King & Queen set (#FPKQ),<BR>
Prince & Princess set (#FPPP),<BR>
Knight & Dragon set (#FPKD),</B>
or collect them all!<BR>
Children ages 9 and up can make these dolls themselves. Adult assistance suggested for
younger children.<P>

<IMG SRC="HandPupp.gif" ALIGN=left><B>Old World Hand Puppet Kits, $19 each, except Baby, $7.50.</B><BR>
One puppet per kit.<BR>
<B>SAVE! Complete set of hand puppets, $99.</B><BR>
While finger puppets like to live in little worlds your child makes for them, hand puppets love the 
spotlight! You can put on complete plays with this cast of charming Old World characters, or just enjoy 
traditional "doll play." Kits come with everything you need: instruction booklet and patterns, wooden 
finger holder, wool stuffing, natural fiber fabrics, embroidery floss, and yarn for the doll's hair. 
Adult puppets, 10". Child puppet, 8". Baby puppet, 5".<BR>
<B>Grandpa (#HPGP), Grandma (#HPGM),  Mamma (#HPM), Poppa (#HPP), Child (#HPC), Baby (#HPB). Complete set (all 6 puppets), #HPX.</B><P>

