<DD>Slightly goofy illustrated instructions AND a yo-yo! <B>#KY</B><P>

<DT><B>Juggling for the Complete Klutz $10.95</B>
<DD>Over 2 million copies sold. Plus 3 cute beanbags. <B>#KJCK</B><P>

<DT><B>Explorabook $18.95</B>
<DD>"A Kids' Science Museum in a Book." 50 science activities. Most can be done with just the book and 
its built-in "surprises." Magnetism (it comes with a magnet), light, growing bacteria, optical 
illusions, and more. <B>#KE</B><P>
</DL>
<H2>THE REST</H2>
<DL>  
<DT><B>Backyard Bird Book $10.95</B>
<DD>Not like those snooty "guides" to birds you've never spotted and never will. Introduce your kids 
to the 28 most common North American species, family favorites like the robin.  <B>#KBB</B><P>

<DT><B>Kids Cooking $13.95</B>
