<A HREF="/CGIs/mapserve.cgi$states.mapfile"><IMG SRC="Smap.gif" ismap
ALT="US map"></A><P>
<H3>This shows all the state level Junior Classical League sites that are
currently on the web, or that I know of.  They're the ones with the red
"bullets" next to the state initials.  Click on the initials to go there,
or on the alternate text links below.  Click on the lightning bolt to bring
you back to the Junior Classical Cyber League home page.  Clicking anywhere
else will just bring you back to this page.</H3><P>
<HR><P>
| <A HREF="http://www-leland.stanford.edu/~feamster">California</A> | <A
HREF="http://www.geocities.com/Athens/8306/mdjcl.html">Maryland</A> | <A
HREF="http://snafu.mit.edu/ncjcl/ncjcl.htm">North Carolina</A> | <A
HREF="http://snafu.mit.edu/ndjcl">North Dakota</A> | <A
HREF="http://snafu.mit.edu/ojcl/home.html">Ohio</A> | <A
HREF="http://www.galstar.com/~scotks">Oklahoma</A> | <A
HREF="http://www.contrib.andrew.cmu.edu/~dscx/jcl/pajcl.html">Pennsylvania</
A> | <A HREF="http://snafu.mit.edu/tsjcl">Texas</A> | <A
HREF="http://www.monmouth.com/user_pages/sporter/jcl.html">JCCL
homepage</A> | <A HREF="http://snafu.mit.edu/njcl/index.html">National
JCL</A> | <A HREF="http://www.umich.edu/~acleague">American Classical
League</A> |
<P><B><IMG SRC="emailed.gif" ALT="little mailbox"> Do you know of any other
state level Junior Classical League sites than the ones listed here?  If
so, please Email me at <A HREF="mailto: Sarah@home-school.com">
Sarah@home-school.com</A> and tell me of it's location?<BR></B>
