<TITLE>Titan - Cronus</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="000000" TEXT="FFFFFF" LINK="E02020" VLINK="C65050">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="titans.gif"><p>
<HR><P>
<H1><B>Cronus</H1></B><P>   Cronus was the youngest of the twelve Titans.  He overthrew his father, Uranus, and became the new ruler of the gods.  <BR>
     He was told by an oracle that his son would overthrow him just like he had overthrown Uranus, so he swallowed all of his children as they were born so that they would be unable to carry out the prophecy.  However, his wife, Rhea, was mad at him for swallowing all her children, so she gave him a rock to swallow instead of the youngest.  This son, Zeus, eventually grew up and overthrew Cronus just like the prophecy had said.<P>
     Cronus' children were the six first Olympians: Zeus, Poseidon, Hades, Hera, Demeter and Hestia, and the only immortal centaur, Chiron.
<P><HR><P>
<A HREF="myth.html">Go back to the main page.</A><P><HR><P>
<H5><I>Created in February of 1997 by Sarah Pride.</H5></I></CENTER>
