<TITLE>Olympian Aphrodite</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" LINK="E02020" VLINK="C65050">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="olympians.gif"><p>
<HR><P>
<H1><B>Aphrodite<BR>(Aff-roe-die-tee)</H1></B><P>   Aphrodite was the goddess of love, beauty and marriage.  There are two stories of how she came to be.  One is that she - happened - when Cronus castrated Uranus and threw part of him into the sea.  Aphrodite rose up from the foam on a large shell.  The other is that she was the daughter of Zeus and Dione.  <BR>  Aphrodite is involved in a lot of Greek mythology.  For example, it was she who, indirectly, caused the Trojan War by persuading Paris to give her the golden apple, and promising the most beautiful woman in the world (Helen) as wife to him.  Also, in another case of golden apples, she gave three of them to Melanion so he could use them to catch Atalanta.  These are only two of many, but most are full of scandals.<BR>  Aphrodite was married to Hephaestus, but she had many affairs.  Her children, by miscellaneous people, are Eros (god of lust), Rhodos, Herophilus, Hermaphroditus, Priapus and Aeneas.  Her sacred tree is myrtle.  Her sacred birds are the dove, swan and sparrow.
<P><HR><P>
<A HREF="myth.html">Go back to the main page.</A><P><HR><P>
