<TITLE>Other gods - Asclepius</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" LINK="E02020" VLINK="C65050">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="other.gif"><p>
<HR><P>
<H1><B>Asclepius<BR>(Az-CLEEP-ee-uss)</H1></B><P><HR><P>
Asclepius was the god of healing.  His parents were Apollo and Coronis.  Now, while Coronis was pregnant with him, she was unfaithful to Apollo.  This was reported to Apollo by a crow, so Apollo, flying into a terrible rage, turned all crows black instead of white, their former color.  Apollo then decided Coronis needed to be executed, and did so. Asclepius, he rescued from her funeral pyre and gave to Chiron, the only immortal centaur, to be raised.  <BR>Chiron, known throughout the land for his wisdom, taught Asclepius the arts of healing, which Asclepius later perfected.<BR>  Later on in his life, Asclepius was given two vials of Gorgon's blood by Athena, one of which would give life, one of which would take it away.  Because he used the life-giving one to raise mortals from the grave, Zeus killed him with a thunder-bolt.  Later, in revenge for his son's life, Apollo killed the Cyclopes that forged the bolt.<P><HR><P>
<A HREF="myth.html">Click here to return to the main Mythology Project page.</A><P><HR><P>
<H5><I>Created in 1996 by Sarah Pride.</H5></I>
