<head>
<title>The Sirens</title>
</head>
<body background="siren.gif" text="#ffffff" link="#ffff00" vlink="#ff00ff"
alink="#ff0000" bgcolor="#000000">
<h1 align="center"><font color="#e60000">The Sirens</font></h1>

<font size="+1"><font color="#00e600">The Sirens were daughters of the sea
god, Phorcys. They had the bodies of birds and the heads
of women and sang so enchantingly that one who listened to them could not
turn away. On the
shore of their island lay the skeletons of many ships' crews which had
fallen captive to their spell.
It is said that when the Argonauts sailed past their island, Orpheus
defeated their charm by singing
a song even more lovelier than theirs. Later, Odysseus according to the
advice of the sorceress,
Circe, had his men stuff their ears with wax to block the deadly song.
Odysseus himself, wishing
to hear their song, had his men tie him to the mast of the ship where he
could not be lured to the
shore. Later legends state that, enraged by these two escapes, the Sirens
threw themselves into the
sea and drowned.</font>

<p><font color="#00e600">                             -Eileen Rebstock
</body>
</html>



